## API and DB conventions (refer to infra packages)

- **TypeScript client API or server API:** Follow the conventions and rules in the **http packages** — see `_thunderstorm/http/` (api-types, client, server). Use their patterns for `ApiDef`, decorators, and request/response typing.
- **DB storable entity:** Follow the conventions and rules in the **db-api package** — see `_thunderstorm/db-api/` (shared, backend, frontend). Use their patterns for CRUD, collections, and persistence.

## BAI (Build and Install)
- always read this: _thunderstorm/build-and-install/.cursor/rules/what-is-bai.mdc
- BAI is the only way to do anything in this repo unless explicitly specified never use pnpm..
- BAI is a CLI tool; it is **not** run via pnpm. Invoke it independently. See **build-and-install rules** for how to run it: [_thunderstorm/build-and-install/.cursor/rules/how-to-use-bai.mdc](_thunderstorm/build-and-install/.cursor/rules/how-to-use-bai.mdc).
- To build `bai -up=<packages-regexp>` (use -up to build specific packaes, otherwise it builds the entire monorepo)
- To run tests `bai -t -tt=<pure|firebase|playwright> -up=<packages-regexp>` (use -up to tests specific packages, otherwise it tests the entire monorepo pakcages)
- To clean install and setup the mono `bai init` (only in extreme case)
- if adding a new package, for fast usability checkout project-structure.mds

